main.model.dict

Class Trie

  • java.lang.Object
    • main.model.dict.Trie

  • class Trie
extends java.lang.Object
    Trie stores strings in a tree structure. Each level represents a position in a string and each branch represents an available character in current position. A string can be seen as the pattern of a search from root to its descendants (not necessarily a leaf, since one word can have another word as prefix).
    See Also:
    TrieNode, WordInfo

      • dfsWithCommonPrefix

        private void dfsWithCommonPrefix(TrieNode node,
                                 java.lang.String target,
                                 int currPos,
                                 java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.String> results,
                                 java.lang.StringBuffer strBuf,
                                 int maxNum)
        Perform DFS upon Trie to retrieve all words with common prefix. This is done by first match the given word then traverse through every word with given word as prefix.
        Parameters:
        node - current node to be searched
        target - target word
        currPos - position to be matched in target word
        results - search result list
        strBuf - string buffer storing DFS path (i.e. part of word)
        maxNum - maximum number of results

      • dfsWithEditDist

        private void dfsWithEditDist(TrieNode node,
                             java.lang.String target,
                             int currPos,
                             java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.String> results,
                             java.lang.StringBuffer strBuf,
                             int editDist)
        Perform DFS upon Trie to retrieve all words with given edit distance. In every step, one edit distance can be consumed by modification (search along another branch), addition (go down in Trie and stay in target), deletion (go forward in target and remain in Trie)
        Parameters:
        node - current node to be searched
        target - target word
        currPos - position to be matched in target word
        results - search result list
        strBuf - string buffer storing DFS path (i.e. part of word)
        editDist - edit distance left
